pageContext.claim: “No, we're at the highest level that they've ever had recorded for a Republican. It's going to be higher, but it's literally, we're beating the Democrats who have been all talk and no action, all talk.”
pageContext.analysis: According to the polling gurus at FiveThirtyEight, roughly 30 percent of Latino voters support the president. That’s about as many who previous Republican candidates. While it is hardly “tremendous,” it is notable that his support has remained consistent despite his rhetoric toward Mexico and other Latin American countries.
